22/08/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- NATO Secretary General Lord Robertson will attend an international conference in Bulgaria in early September, according to the organisers of the event, the Centre for Research of Democracy. 
The defence ministers of Central and East European countries, as well as top EU officials, are also expected.
In other news, the Association of History Teachers in Bulgaria said the final seminar in a joint project launched by Albania, Bulgaria and Macedonia opens on Friday (22 August). 
The project involves compiling a common history handbook for teachers. 
It marks the first time educators from the three countries have overcome differences in the interpretation of facts, using parallel presentations of different viewpoints. 
(Dnevnik, Trud, 24 Chassa - 22/08/03; BTA, BNR- 21/08/03)
